  "texts": [
    "Although tRNA-Arg-UCU-4-1 was strongly upregulated in neurons (approximately 40% of tRNA-Arg-UCU), the abundance of this anticodon family decreased by approximately 1.4-fold because other isodecoders were downregulated (Extended Data Fig. 1k,l and Supplementary Table 1).",
    "Thus, despite extensive reprogramming of tRNA transcript pools, the availability of tRNA anticodons in human cells remains largely unchanged following differentiation.",
    "Codon usage and decoding rates do not vary across cell typesWe next investigated whether the small but significant differences in tRNA anticodon pools among cell types are linked to differences in codon demand as previous studies on its potential coordination with tRNA supply have reached conflicting conclusions 17,18,38.",
    "Codon usage weighted for expression correlated significantly with tRNA anticodon abundance (Pearson's correlation coefficient (r) = 0.57-0.66; Fig. 2a) and was strikingly stable across all four cell types (coefficient of variation (CV), 0.77-13.22%; Fig.",
    "2b), in accordance with previous data from mouse and human tissues 17,18."
